data.title: The Range Planet
data.text:
Post by Steve on

Voice Type: Barechest Baritenor

Vocal Range: B1 - C6

Significant High Notes:

C6 ("Rock and Roll")

A5 ("Magic Bus" Live)

G5 ("New Song", "Won't Get Fooled Again")

F♯5 ("Twist and Shout" Live Isle of Wight 1970)

F5 ("Free Me", "Join Together", "Love Reign O'er Me", "Shout and Shimmy")

E5 ("5.15", "Avening Annie", "Cooks County", "Giddy", "I'm Free", "It's a Hard Life", "Kashmir", "Put the Money Down", "Relay", "Rock and Roll", "Sea and Sand", "Summertime Blues" Live at Leeds, "Won't Get Fooled Again", "Young Man Blues" Live at Young Vic)

E♭5 ("(Come and) Get Your Love", "Guitar and Pen", "Join Together", "Let's See Action (Nothing Is Everything)", "Love Reign O'er Me", "One Man Band", "Proud", "The Real Me" Alternate, "Say It Ain't So, Joe")

D5 ("5.15", "Baba O'Riley", "Balance on Wires", "Bell Boy", "Blues Man's Road", "Can't Wait to See the Movie", "Christmas", "Cut My Hair", "Dear Love", "Don't Let Go the Coat", "Everything a Heart Could Ever Want (Willow)", "Feeling", "Free Me", "Getting in Tune", "Helpless Dancer", "I'm Free", "It's a Hard Life", "I've Had Enough", "Judas' Death", "Keep it Out of Sight", "Lover's Storm", "Magic Bus" Live, "Miracle of Love", "Music Must Change", "Near to Surrender", "One of the Boys", "Raglan Road", "Young Man Blues" Live at Leeds, "Sally Simpson", "Saturday Night's Alright for Fighting", "Slip Kid", "Walking in My Sleep", "Walking the Dog", "Who Are You", "World Over", "You Can't Call It Love", "You Put Something Better Inside of Me")

C♯5 "Armenia City in the Sky", "Call Me Lightning", "Can’t Explain" Live at Leeds, "Child of Mine", "Don't Let the Sun Go Down on Me", "The Heart Has Its Reasons", "I Am the Sea", "Love Ain't For Keeping" New York Record Plant Session, "Mirror Mirror", "No More Mr. Nice Guy", "Peace At Last", "Perfect World", "Put the Money Down", "Ready for Love", "Say It Ain't So Joe", "The Song Is Over", "Times Changed", "Too Much of Anything")

C5 ("Alone in the Night", "Anyway, Anyhow, Anywhere", "Armenia City in the Sky", "Athena", "Baba O'Riley", "Baby, Don’t You Do It", "Before My Time Is Up", "Born to Run", "(Come and) Get Your Love", "Dangerous", "Did You Steal My Money?", "The Dirty Jobs", "Dreaming from the Waist", “Eyesight to the Blind (The Hawker)”, "Free Me", "Getting in Tune", "Had Enough", "Hearts Right", "Heaven on Their Minds", "How Many Friends", "Ice on the Motorway", "In a Hand or Face", "Is It in My Head?", "Is There Anybody Out There?", "It's in You", "I've Known No War", "Join Together", "Keep on Loving You", "Let's See Action (Nothing Is Everything)", "Love Is Coming Down", "My Generation", "Never Make Your Move Too Soon", "New Song", "Out in the Street", "The Price of Love", "Quicksilver Lightning", "Ready for Love", "The Real Me", "Saturday Night's Alright for Fighting", "Sea and Sand", "Shout and Shimmy", "The Song is Over", "There Is Love", "Thinking", "Under a Raging Moon", "Water" Live, "Who's Gonna Walk on Water", "Won't Get Fooled Again", "You", "You Are Yourself", "You Better You Bet")

B4 ("A Quick One, While He’s Away" Live at Leeds, "Bald Headed Woman", "Black Widow’s Eyes", "Bucket T", "Cooks County", "Daddy Rolling Stone", "How Can You Do It Alone", "How Does the Cold Wind Cry", "I Can't Explain", "Imagine a Man", "I'm a Man", "Is There Anybody Out There?", "It's a Hard Life", "It’s Hard", "I Want It All" Live Freddie Mercury Tribute Concert 1992, "Let it Be" Live, "Love Ain’t for Keeping", "Love Hurts" Live 2/7/1989, "Love Me Like You Do", "Magic Bus", "Parting Should be Painless", "Please, Please, Please", "Summertime Blues" Live at Leeds, "They Are All In Love", "Twist and Shout" Live Isle of Wight 1970, "Walking in My Sleep", "Who Are You", "Young Man Blues" Live at Leeds)

B♭4 ("Athena", "Baby, Don’t You Do It", "Bargain", "Daddy Rolling Stone", “Eyesight to the Blind (The Hawker)”, "I Don’t Even Know Myself", "It’s Your Turn", "Keep it Out of Sight", "Keep on Loving You", "The Real Me", "Slip Kid", "Sneaking Suspicion", "Somebody Told Me", "The Song is Over", "Squeeze Box", "You Better You Bet")

Significant Low Notes:

C3 ("Another Tricky Day", "In a Hand or Face", "It’s Hard", "Magic Bus" Live at Leeds, "Rael (1 and 2)")

B2 ("A Quick One, While He's Away", "Bitter & Twisted", "Black Widow’s Eyes", "Faith in Something Bigger", "The Good's Gone", "I'm the Face", "Mack the Knife", "Magic Bus", "Martyrs and Madmen", "Mirror Mirror", "Relax", "See My Way", "Walking in My Sleep")

B♭2 ("Everybody’s Carrying a Gun", "I Can See for Miles", "It's Not True")

A2 ("A Quick One, While He's Away", "Bitter & Twisted", "The Good's Gone", "I'm a Man", "Johnny Cash Medley" Live, "Love Ain’t for Keeping", "One Day", "Walking in My Sleep", "Wheels on the Bus")

G2 ("Bald Headed Woman", "Barbara Ann", "Big Boss Man" Live New York ’79, "Daddy Rolling Stone", "Don't Wait on the Stairs", "Everybody on the Bus", "Fragments", "Much Too Much", "My Generation" Live, "Wheels on the Bus")

F♯2 ("The Good's Gone", "How Can You Do It Alone", "I Can See for Miles", "Times Changed")

F2 ("Bald Headed Woman", "Music Must Change")

E2 ("Child of Mine", "Johnny Cash Medley" Live, "Mirror Door", "Take Me Home", "Who's Gonna Walk on Water")

E♭2 ("High, Low, Fast, Slow", "Somebody Told Me")

D2 ("Music Must Change", "Johnny Cash Medley" Live)

C2 ("High, Low, Fast, Slow")

B1 ("Mirror Door")

.......................................................

*Underlined marks notes in backing vocals or otherwise muffled/obscured in the song mix.

*Blue marks powerful, clear falsetto notes.

*Italics mark non-melodic notes.

*Grey marks heavily fryish notes.

Best Vocal Performances:

Studio:

1. Love, Reign O'er Me

2. Free Me

3. Baba O'Riley

4. Say It Ain't So, Joe

5. Love Is Coming Down

6. Bargain

7. I'm Free

8. (Come and) Get Your Love

9. Rock and Roll

10. It’s a Hard Life

{Album Ranges}The Who:

My Generation (Deluxe Edition) (1965) (F2 - C5 - F5)

A Quick One (1966) (B2 - A4)

The Who Sell Out (1967) (F♯2 - C♯5)

Tommy (1969) (G3 - C5)

Who's Next (1971) (A2 - G5)

Quadrophenia (1973) (E3 - E5)

The Who by Numbers (1975) (E3 - D5)

Who Are You (1978) (D2 - E♭5 - G5)

Face Dances (1981) (F♯2 - D5)

It's Hard (1982) (C3 - B4 - E5)

Endless Wire (2006) (G2 - A4 - B4)

Solo:

Daltrey (1973)

Ride a Rock Horse (1975)

One of the Boys (1977)

McVicar (1980)

Parting Should Be Painless (1984) (E♭2 - D5)

Under a Raging Moon (1985)
